  "article_paragraphs": [
    {
      "number": 1,
      "text": "Dolphins live in the ocean. They look like fish, but they are not fish. They are mammals like us. Dolphins must come to the surface to breathe air. They have a special hole on top of their heads to help them breathe."
    },
    {
      "number": 2,
      "text": "Dolphins are very friendly and playful animals. They love to jump high out of the water. They often swim next to boats. They live in family groups called pods. Dolphins talk to each other using clicks and whistles."
    },
    {
      "number": 3,
      "text": "Dolphins are also very smart. They can learn tricks and help people. Sometimes, dolphins save swimmers who are in danger. Everyone loves to watch dolphins play in the blue sea."
    }
